<item>
            <title>[OWB-480] Avoid a couple NPEs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OWB-480</link>
                <project id="12310844" key="OWB">OpenWebBeans</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve found 2 possible NPE;s:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. in an OSGI environment, its quite possible that no openwebbeans.properties files will be located, so you get a null properties object and OpenWebBeansConfiguration will have a null Properties leading to big problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. in WebContainerLifecycle, the claim that it&apos;s a jsp app by configuration might be wrong.  If there&apos;s no jsp factory, no need to throw an NPE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
